                                        <q xml:lang="is">
                                            <name type="person" key="JonEin007">Jon Eynar son</name>
                                                heff<expan>ur</expan>…</q>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <locus>27v</locus> (sixteenth century?): <q xml:lang="is"
                                            >Hallvr Ein<expan>a</expan>rsson</q>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <locus>28v</locus> (seventeenth century): <q xml:lang="is"
                                            >Halla teiks dotter Eigin hand þo styrdar sie
                                            syngurnar</q>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <locus>31r</locus> (sixteenth or seventeenth century): <q
                                            xml:lang="is">Fridur sie med ydur nu <expan>og</expan>
                                                jafnan<expan>n</expan> min<expan>n</expan> gode vin
                                                <name type="person" key="KetKet001">ketill
                                                ketelsson</name>
                                        </q>
                                    </item>
                                </list> None of these names can be identfied. </p>
                        </additions>
                        <accMat>
                            <p>A note pasted to the front of the manuscript reads: <q xml:lang="is"
                                    >Olafs Saga Helga komin til min fra <name type="person"
                                        key="JonBod001">Jone Bdvars syne</name>. <hi
                                        rend="underline">ut puto</hi>. imò non dubito. Eg feck eina
                                    Olafs Sgu fra honum, og kann þad eingin nnur ad vera enn
                                    þesse</q> Another AM-slip concerning f. 37 reads: <q
                                    xml:lang="is">feinged af Monsr <name type="person"
                                        key="JonTho008">Jone Þorkelssyni</name> fra <name
                                        type="place">Niardvik</name>, 1719 i <name type="place"
                                        key="Copen01">Kaupenhafn</name>, En<expan>n</expan>
                                        h<expan>onu</expan>m var þ<expan>ad</expan> sendt fra
                                    Islande sama är. hafde vered utanum eitt hans kver þar, og hafde
                                        han<expan>n</expan> svo epter þvi bod girt</q>
                            </p>
                        </accMat>
